# Comprehensive Profile Setup Overhaul

Transform the basic 3-field profile setup into an industry-standard, multi-step professional onboarding wizard that deeply understands the user's capabilities, experience, and work preferences — enabling the AI leader to assign roles and tasks with surgical precision.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Schema expansion**: The `User` model currently stores `skills` (JSON), `domains` (JSON), and `level` (enum). This plan adds a new `profileData` (JSON) column to store all the extended profile information without breaking existing AI assignment logic. The existing `skills`, `domains`, and `level` fields remain as-is for backward compatibility.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Resume upload**: This uses browser-side FileReader to parse the resume into text (for PDF preview/display). The actual file is uploaded to the server as base64, then stored as a URL via Vercel Blob. If Vercel Blob is not yet configured, the resume file will be stored as base64 in the `profileData` JSON field temporarily. Let me know your preference.

> [!WARNING]
> **This is a frontend-heavy change.** The profile setup page grows from ~200 lines to ~1200+ lines across multiple components. The API route changes are minimal (accepting the new `profileData` field). No other pages are affected.

## Open Questions

1. **Resume storage**: Should the resume be uploaded to Vercel Blob (requires `BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN` env var), or stored as metadata only (extracted text stored in DB, no file storage)?
2. **Profile editability**: Should users be able to re-visit and edit their profile after initial setup, or is it one-time only? Currently there's no edit page — only the setup page with a hard block.
3. **Minimum completion**: Should all 6 steps be mandatory, or should only Steps 1-3 be required and Steps 4-6 optional?

