## Proposed Changes

### Database Schema

#### [MODIFY] [schema.prisma](file:///j:/PaceUp/prisma/schema.prisma)

Add a `profileData` JSON column to the `User` model:

```diff
 model User {
   id        String     @id @default(cuid())
   clerkId   String     @unique
   userCode  String?    @unique @db.VarChar(8)
   name      String
   email     String     @unique
   skills    Json       @default("[]")
   domains   Json       @default("[]")
   level     UserLevel?
+  profileData Json?
+  resumeUrl   String?  @db.Text
   createdAt DateTime   @default(now())
   ...
 }
```

The `profileData` JSON will store the full extended profile:

```typescript
interface ExtendedProfileData {
  // Step 1: Personal Overview
  headline: string;              // "Full-Stack Developer | ML Enthusiast"
  bio: string;                   // 2-3 sentence professional summary
  location: string;              // City, Country
  linkedinUrl?: string;
  githubUrl?: string;
  portfolioUrl?: string;

  // Step 2: Technical Skills (granular)
  languageProficiencies: Array<{
    language: string;
    proficiency: "BEGINNER" | "INTERMEDIATE" | "ADVANCED" | "EXPERT";
    yearsOfExperience: number;
  }>;
  frameworks: string[];
  tools: string[];               // Git, Docker, Figma, etc.
  databases: string[];
  cloudPlatforms: string[];

  // Step 3: Professional Experience
  currentRole: string;           // "Student" | "Intern" | "Junior Dev" | etc.
  yearsOfExperience: number;
  education: string;             // "B.Tech CS" | "M.Sc." | etc.
  previousProjects: Array<{
    name: string;
    description: string;
    role: string;
    techStack: string[];
  }>;

  // Step 4: Work Style & Preferences
  preferredRole: string[];       // "Team Lead" | "Backend Dev" | "Designer" | etc.
  communicationStyle: string;    // "Async-first" | "Meetings" | "Hybrid"
  availabilityHoursPerWeek: number;
  timezone: string;
  preferredWorkSchedule: string; // "Morning" | "Afternoon" | "Night Owl" | "Flexible"
  teamSizePreference: string;   // "Solo" | "Small (2-4)" | "Medium (5-8)" | "Large (9+)"

  // Step 5: Goals & Aspirations
  learningGoals: string[];       // What they want to learn from projects
  careerGoals: string;           // Short-term career direction
  challengePreference: string;   // "Comfort Zone" | "Stretch" | "Deep End"
  feedbackPreference: string;    // "Direct & Blunt" | "Constructive" | "Encouraging"

  // Step 6: Resume (optional)
  hasResume: boolean;
}
```

