**Step 3 — Professional Experience** (Your journey so far)
- Current role — select (Student, Intern, Junior Developer, Mid-Level Developer, Senior Developer, Tech Lead, Designer, Product Manager, Researcher, Other)
- Years of coding experience — slider (0-15+)
- Education — text input
- Previous projects — dynamic form (add/remove): project name, description, your role, tech stack tags
- Up to 3 projects

**Step 4 — Work Style & Preferences** (How do you work best?)
- Preferred team roles — multi-select (Team Lead, Backend Developer, Frontend Developer, Full-Stack Developer, DevOps Engineer, UI/UX Designer, Data Scientist, QA/Tester, Documentation, Project Manager)
- Communication style — single select cards (Async-first, Meeting-oriented, Hybrid)
- Weekly availability — slider (1-40+ hours)
- Timezone — select dropdown
- Preferred work schedule — select cards (Early Bird, Afternoon, Night Owl, Flexible)
- Team size preference — select cards (Solo, Small 2-4, Medium 5-8, Large 9+)

**Step 5 — Goals & Aspirations** (Where are you heading?)
- Learning goals — tag input (What skills do you want to develop?)
- Career direction — textarea (Where do you see yourself in 2 years?)
- Challenge preference — select cards (Comfort Zone, Stretch Goals, Deep End)
- Feedback preference — select cards (Direct & Blunt, Constructive & Detailed, Encouraging & Supportive)

**Step 6 — Resume Upload** (Optional — supercharge your profile)
- Drag & drop zone for PDF/DOCX
- File size limit: 5MB
- Shows upload progress
- Preview of uploaded filename
- Skip button clearly visible
- Disclaimer: "Your resume helps the AI leader understand your full background for better task assignment. It is stored securely and never shared."

**Wizard UI Elements:**
- Step indicator / progress bar at the top showing all 6 steps
- Back / Next buttons with validation per step
- Step titles with icons
- Smooth slide transitions between steps
- "Save & Continue Later" option (saves partial progress)
- Final review step before submission

